{"type":"message","id":"2cd75c25","parentId":"d4fdf284","timestamp":"2026-03-13T04:22:58.948Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[cron:062553b9-d784-4b0e-a48e-3a56fc479ad9 img-gen-2-queue-check] CHECK_IMG_QUEUE: Check the image generation queue and process any pending requests. Run: node /data/img-gen/img-claim.js img-gen-2 — if a request is returned (not null), process it following your SOUL.md workflow. Generate the image in Gemini, download it, call img-complete.js when done, then check the queue again for more pending requests.\nCurrent time: Friday, March 13th, 2026 — 12:22 PM (Asia/Kuala_Lumpur)\n\nReturn your summary as plain text; it will be delivered automatically. If the task explicitly calls for messaging a specific external recipient, note who/where it should go instead of sending it yourself."}],"timestamp":1773375778945}}
{"type":"message","id":"e861b0fd","parentId":"2cd75c25","timestamp":"2026-03-13T04:23:09.428Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Okay, let's see. The user is asking me to check the image generation queue and process any pending requests. The cron job is set up to run this every so often. The main script to use is /data/img-gen/img-claim.js with the agent name img-gen-2.\n\nFirst, I need to run that command. If it returns a request (not null), then I have to follow the SOUL.md workflow. Let me recall the steps from SOUL.md. The workflow is: claim a request, get the MultiLogin X profile ID, craft a prompt, generate the image, mark it as complete or failed.\n\nSo, step 1: Run node /data/img-gen/img-claim.js img-gen-2. If the output is null, the queue is empty. If not, proceed to the next steps.\n\nAssuming there's a request, next is getting the profile ID. The command given is node -e \"const c=JSON.parse(require('fs').readFileSync('/data/img-gen/google-accounts.json','utf8')); console.log(c['img-gen-2'].mlProfileId);\". So I need to run that to get the profile ID.\n\nThen, refine the prompt using the Image Prompting Guide. The guide says to structure the prompt with subject, action, setting, style, lighting, camera angle, mood, quality markers. For example, LinkedIn photos need specific details like corporate headshot, lighting, background, etc.\n\nAfter crafting the prompt, generate the image in Gemini. The exact steps for Gemini are in the SKILL.md, but since the user is in img-gen-2, I should follow that.\n\nOnce the image is generated, download it and mark the request as complete using img-complete.js with the success or failure details.\n\nBut the current task is just to check the queue and process any pending requests. The user's cron job is triggered, so I need to check the queue first.\n\nWait, the user's instruction says: \"Run: node /data/img-gen/img-claim.js img-gen-2 — if a request is returned (not null), process it following your SOUL.md workflow.\"\n\nSo the first step is to execute that command. If there's a request, proceed to process it. If not, exit.\n\nSo the first action is to call exec with the command to run the claim script.\n\nPossible scenario: the queue has a request, so we get a JSON object with request details. Then, proceed to get the profile ID, craft the prompt, generate, etc.\n\nBut since the task is to check the queue and process any pending requests, the initial step is to run the claim script.\n\nLet me check the tools available. The exec function is available. So I should use exec to run the command.\n\nThe command is: node /data/img-gen/img-claim.js img-gen-2\n\nIf this returns a non-null value, then process it. If null, stop.\n\nBut the user is asking for a summary, so after checking the queue, if there's a request, process it and return the summary.\n\nWait, the user is expecting a summary of what was done. So in the case where a request is found, we need to outline the steps taken to process it.\n\nBut the user's message is a cron job triggered task. So the assistant should check the queue, process any requests, and then return a summary.\n\nSo first step: run the claim script.\n\nPossible outputs:\n\n- If null: queue empty, summary says \"Queue empty. No requests processed.\"\n\n- If not null: process the request, generate image, mark complete, then repeat until queue empty.\n\nAssuming the queue has requests, the next steps are to get the profile ID, craft the prompt, generate, download, and mark complete.\n\nBut the actual processing would involve the browser control (HumanBrowser) as per the SOUL.md.\n\nWait, SOUL.md says: \"You have your own dedicated Google account pre-logged into Gemini inside your MultiLogin X profile. You use the HumanBrowser system to operate the browser.\"\n\nSo, the steps after getting the profile ID would be to use the browser to navigate to Gemini and generate the image.\n\nBut the user's query here is the cron job to check the queue and process requests. So the immediate step is to run the claim script.\n\nTherefore, the first action is to call exec with the command to claim a request.\n\nLet me write the exec command.\n\nCommand: node /data/img-gen/img-claim.js img-gen-2\n\nIf this returns a non-null value, then proceed to get the profile ID.\n\nSo, the tool call would be to exec that command.\n\nAfter executing, the response would be a JSON string. If it's not null, parse it to get the request details.\n\nThen, get the profile ID from the google-accounts.json file.\n\nThen, proceed with the prompt crafting and image generation.\n\nBut the user's task here is to check the queue and process pending requests, so the summary should indicate whether there were requests and what was done.\n\nSince the user is expecting a summary, the assistant needs to output a plain text summary of the actions taken.\n\nSo, in this case, the first step is to run the claim script. If it returns a request, process it and note the outcome.\n\nGiven that the user is in the context of img-gen-2, and the SOUL.md specifies the workflow, the correct approach is to first check the queue.\n\nSo, the first tool call is exec to run the claim script.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_827a234a0cfb4e8ab0b92f","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"node /data/img-gen/img-claim.js img-gen-2","pty":true}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"qwen/qwen3-vl-30b-a3b-thinking","usage":{"input":12526,"output":2298,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":14824,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773375778947}}
